commitResults.messageTitle: Side note, I didn't realise i had to commit A-TextUiTesting and A-Enums, so I didnt do the textUiTesting properly until this commit, and enums were used since the level-5 commit. Will take proper note of the correct commit sequence moving forward
Duke.java: Add loadData and saveData functions
Duke Class: Update position of saveData() function in main()
commitResults.messageBody:
The duke.txt file is supposed to be updated for every change made to
the list. Hence, the saveData() function has been moved to reflect this.
Prior to this, the .txt file would only be updated at the end of the
interaction with the Duke chat box when they use the command "bye".

commitResults.messageTitle: Deadline and Event class: use java.time.LocalDateTime
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline and event classes now save their times as
java.time.LocalDateTime objects.

This is to enable destiny to understand dates and times. As such,
destiny is now able to do the following:
* display the date and time in a standardized manner
* for events, ensure start time is a date and time before end time

Now uses instance of Duke class instead of running duke from a static
context. This is to make the code more object oriented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Duke class: Extract functions into classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Extracted the following from the duke class:
* loading and saving of tasks in the data file (Storage.java)
* making sense of the user command (Parser.java)
* the taskList, and operations that manipulate it (TaskList.java)

This was done to make the code more object oriented

Changed the automated tests to adjust for the recent changes to
the code and how it responds to correct and incorrect inputs.
